snippet.textDisplay: I am tired of trying to answer all the individual posts that are commenting on the devastation that is happening in my country so lightly. I respect you have a right to your viewpoint on climate change but to make comments without really looking into what is really happening here is thoughtless. Our country is burning, people are dying, homes are being lost, we have lost almost a billion of our precious wildlife and millions of our domestic animals and pets. Our crops have been destroyed and whole towns wiped out, everyone is stressed as most of us have bush land around us that can go up in flames at any time. Yet what do we read, it’s not climate change it’s just arsonists! Yes people have been arrested, but people are arrested every year in Australia for arson and starting bushfires its nothing new for us, many of those arrested are not for deliberate arson but for careless action that has either led to a fire or could have led to a fire such as throwing a still lit cigarette butt away, burning off debris on a no fire day, not all arrested were deliberate arsonists. Everyone agrees there are combined reasons for the horrendous fires this year such as insufficient back burning but one of the acknowledged reasons is the unprecedented high temperatures that country experienced in December where we had temperatures of up to 5-10 degrees Celsius above the average on many days. The large fires also cause their own weather front causing lightning strikes which start more fires. I acknowledge that many people in the world do not believe in climate change but living in Australia we are seeing it in our lives and perhaps that is what it will take for others to accept it as well. The Australian people on the whole believe in climate change our scientists and meteorologists acknowledge climate change, these fires show the world that climate change is real yet still doubt it. Sir Richard Attenborough says we have approximately ten years to change and try and salvage the planet after that it may be irreversible but after what I have read here in these comments I fear ten years will not be sufficient time to change the mind of most. Please view the clips of the people who are fighting the fires and who are rescuing and looking after our wildlife and see the fires and how large they are and research more and think more before you comment.

At the end of November 2018, Canadian Human Rights Attorney David Matas visited Israel for the second time last year to lecture at the UNESCO 13th World Conference on Bioethics, Medical Ethics and Health Law in Jerusalem.

Mr. Matas lectured on the ethical aspects of a long and comprehensive investigation of the issue of forced organ harvesting in China, which is being carried out by the ruling regime itself. The main victims of this practice are Falun Gong (also called Falun Dafa) practitioners. Falun Gong is a traditional spiritual discipline that abides by the principles of Truthfulness-Compassion-Forbearance and has been persecuted by the Chinese regime since 1999.
